00:43:52,040 --> 00:43:54,160
We're struggling on our own.

542
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:56,320
Thank you for your time, Pond.

543
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:58,160
It does not waste my time at all.

544
00:43:58,520 --> 00:43:59,360
On the other hand,

545
00:44:00,240 --> 00:44:02,360
It's like a review for me too.

546
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:08,000
Tutoring Kun and Korn is like helping my own brother.
I've known them since they were this small.

547
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:12,240
Tod, just relax, okay?

548
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:15,000
Thanks, Teacher Nick. Oh...

549
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:16,120
Teacher Pond.

550
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:17,440
Alright.

551
00:44:17,720 --> 00:44:20,160
Let me know if you need anything.

552
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:25,040
If they pass, you'll get a bonus, Pond.

553
00:44:25,200 --> 00:44:27,640
No need, Mrs. Kaew.

554
00:44:28,080 --> 00:44:30,080
Happy to help. We're like family.

555
00:44:35,040 --> 00:44:37,440
Is it okay to have Pond as a tutor?

556
00:44:38,920 --> 00:44:43,160
Better than now. I can't manage your laziness alone.

557
00:44:44,800 --> 00:44:47,720
Worried it might be too strict.

558
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:52,000
Just give it a shot. Pond's smart.

559
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:54,360
What are you two whispering about?

560
00:44:54,920 --> 00:44:56,200
Nothing.

561
00:44:57,280 --> 00:44:59,200
Just eat.

562
00:45:07,200 --> 00:45:08,600
Ouch, I hurt my stomach.

563
00:45:09,560 --> 00:45:10,480
I'll go to the bathroom first.

564
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:13,920
Bet he's off to play games.

565
00:45:14,440 --> 00:45:16,000
See you later, Pond.

566
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:17,840
Take care!

567
00:45:20,280 --> 00:45:21,120
That's just how he is,

568
00:45:21,560 --> 00:45:22,480
don't mind him.

569
00:45:25,120 --> 00:45:29,400
Can't believe how fast they've grown.

570
00:45:31,280 --> 00:45:34,520
I really wanted you to tutor because of Korn.

571
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:39,560
Kun keeps complaining about dragging him to study.

572
00:45:39,760 --> 00:45:41,400
All he does is complain about laziness.

573
00:45:43,880 --> 00:45:44,800
He's always like that.

574
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:48,640
When's the next exam, Kun?

575
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,320
In two months.

576
00:45:52,400 --> 00:45:54,200
In two months...

577
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:56,560
Should be enough time then.

578
00:45:57,640 --> 00:45:59,080
Tod and I are stressed out.

579
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:00,920
We're not keeping up.

580
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:04,320
It's scary when it doesn't match our studies.

581
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:09,040
Just relax, no need to overthink.

582
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:13,200
-Kun is not a concern.
-Yes, ma'am.

583
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:16,880
But Korn, I don't know what to do with him.

584
00:46:21,720 --> 00:46:24,640
Tomorrow... oh, Saturday right?

585
00:46:25,960 --> 00:46:28,320
How about this? I'll start tutoring here from tomorrow afternoon.

586
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:32,040
Kun, Tod!

587
00:46:32,880 --> 00:46:35,400
You guys okay with that? Any plans this weekend?

588
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:39,240
Was planning to study at home anyway.

589
00:46:39,560 --> 00:46:41,360
Let's start tomorrow then.

590
00:46:41,800 --> 00:46:43,280
Sounds good, it's a deal.

591
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:48,040
Feel free to be firm with Korn.

592
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,640
I'll check on him upstairs.

593
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:56,920
-Kun, please take care of him.
-Yes, sure.

594
00:46:57,400 --> 00:47:01,040
Mrs. Kaew, I should head out now.

595
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:03,600
Don't want to get home too late.

596
00:47:04,880 --> 00:47:06,440
Thanks, Pond. See you tomorrow.

597
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:08,280
Until tomorrow.

598
00:47:08,520 --> 00:47:10,040
See you tomorrow.

599
00:47:10,560 --> 00:47:12,520
Goodbye, Mrs. Kaew.

600
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:14,920
-Goodbye!
-Bye, take care!

601
00:47:15,520 --> 00:47:16,320
Thank you, see you later.

602
00:47:19,720 --> 00:47:21,360
We can mix this.

603
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:23,920
I'll keep these dishes.

604
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:32,640
All washed.

605
00:47:38,680 --> 00:47:40,600
Why does Korn seem to dislike me?

606
00:47:43,240 --> 00:47:44,480
What makes you say that?

607
00:47:45,520 --> 00:47:46,760
Isn't it obvious?

608
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:49,960
That's just how he is.

609
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:51,640
It's his personality.

610
00:47:52,760 --> 00:47:55,160
He finds it hard to get close to people.

611
00:47:57,920 --> 00:48:03,240
Mother said that you and Kun never fight. Is that true?

612
00:48:05,920 --> 00:48:07,440
I usually make up first.

613
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:09,960
which coincides with Kun's sulking.

614
00:48:12,920 --> 00:48:15,720
Are you normally sulky?

615
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:20,560
Someone once told me I'm sulky.

616
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:23,120
and hard to get close to.

617
00:48:24,560 --> 00:48:27,080
And I don't really care about others' feelings.

618
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:29,520
Do I remind you of Korn?

619
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:36,840
Korn's just like that. No worries.

620
00:48:45,440 --> 00:48:47,840
Mom recently shared some childhood stories.

621
00:48:48,560 --> 00:48:50,960
What did she say?

622
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:53,360
She said...

623
00:48:55,200 --> 00:48:57,720
Korn and I, we used to play together.

624
00:48:58,280 --> 00:49:01,200
I once played a prank on Kun by sticking his hand in a socket.

625
00:49:02,040 --> 00:49:02,960
Pretty mean, huh?

626
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:06,600
I see.

627
00:49:07,120 --> 00:49:07,680
Why?

628
00:49:08,160 --> 00:49:11,280
Is that why you guys developed a fear of electric shocks?

629
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:14,560
Maybe... I don't know.

630
00:49:15,120 --> 00:49:16,280
But that's harsh.

631
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:18,800
Actually, there's more.

632
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:23,360
Once, many years ago,  Kun pranked me back

633
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:25,280
by stuffing meatballs in my mouth.

634
00:49:26,280 --> 00:49:27,480
I almost choked.

635
00:49:27,800 --> 00:49:29,240
It was a close call to the hospital.

636
00:49:30,120 --> 00:49:31,040
That's also harsh.

637
00:49:31,360 --> 00:49:33,360
How did you guys survive childhood?

638
00:49:36,680 --> 00:49:40,120
Just kids being silly. Luckily, no harm done.

639
00:49:41,280 --> 00:49:50,480
Those two incidents brought us closer.

640
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:56,680
Nothing ever big enough to make us really fight.

